		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Skills &amp; Earning Money<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Fri, Jul 6th 3:47 PM2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=10&mid=9944488525907&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=10&mid=9944488525907&num=4&page=&post=1&replyto=9944488525907"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=9944488525907></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=73397"><span id=>Liska</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>1 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Liska&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Okay, I'm a (half-naked) Half Elf Ranger (LVL3) and I have a few questions for the more experienced Rangers out there.<br><br>I've heard about allocating extra points earned to various skills to save time in bringing them to a higher level.&nbsp;&nbsp;Is this actually possible, or did I just misunderstand something?  Is it only available at higher levels?  I can upgrade my various skills pretty fast, but if this could speed it up, I'm all for that!<br><br>Also, I have no mana, and I understood that Rangers eventually learn to cast.  Will I get mana when I learn to cast?<br><br>One more.  I am currently in and around Kelethin, and I was wondering the most profitable trade skill in this area to invest time and money in learning?<br><br>Oops, sorry, one more.  I am currently carrying a Rusty Spear to upgrade my piercing skills, it seemed like a good ratio of damage to delay.  Is this a good choice for piercing?<br><br>Okay, that's all.  Thanks so much in advance for answering.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Liska<br>3rd Level Ranger<br>Vazaelle Server</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >4 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Fri, Jul 6th 9:44 PM2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=10&mid=9944488525907&num=4&page=&post=1&replyto=99447027411250"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=99447027411250></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=11679"><span id=Scholar>Martelus</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br>45 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.80]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Martelus&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>-As you level you will be able to train in new skills.&nbsp;&nbsp;You will need to go to your guild trainer and check out what you can learn.  If you just turned level 3 you can now learn the FORAGE skill.  I will list the other skill you will eventually learn:<br><br>LEVEL 5 ---&gt;KICK<br>LEVEL 8 ---&gt;DODGE<br>LEVEL 9---&gt;ABJURATION, ALTERATION, CONJURATION, DIVINATION, EVOCATION (Your magic                    skills).  You do NOT need to learn CHANNELLING.  You get it automatically at 9.                     BTW, this is when you gain mana and can begin casting spells.  Be sure you buy all                    your level 9 spells.  You will gain new spells at level 9, level 15, level 22, level 30,                    level 39, level 49 and every level from 50 to 60.<br>LEVEL 10--&gt;SNEAK<br>LEVEL 12--&gt;MEDITATION<br>LEVEL 17--&gt;DUAL WIELD<br>LEVEL 18--&gt;PARRY<br>LEVEL 20--&gt;DOUBLE ATTACK<br>LEVEL 25--&gt;HIDE<br>LEVEL 35--&gt;DISARM & REPOSTE<br><br>What people mean by allocating extra points to a skill is this.   Every time you make a level you gain 5 additional training points at you guild trainer.  You can use these points to learn a new skill when you reach the level listed above, and/or you can increase a skill you already know, or just leaned, by spending the training points on them.  Some skills are harder to raise, through use, than others.  Some skills you just want to get as high as possible, as quickly as possible.  To do this, you need to use your training points to increase a skill.  The skill most Rangers pump up is DUAL WIELD AND/OR DOUBLE ATTACK.  They save thier training points for level 17 when they can learn dual wield, and use 1 point to learn the skill, then pump another 30 to 50 training points into DUAL WIELD to get it up to a higher level where it works better.<br><br>Here are some additional notes about training skills. <br><br>1) When you reach a level that you can learn a new skill, that skill will have a beginning level, when you train, equal to the level you learn it at.  Example:  You train in Dual Wield at 17.  If you just used 1 training point to learn this skill, you will begin with a skill of 17 in Dual Wield.  If you should happen to wait until level 23 to learn Dual Wield, when you do train in it, you will begin with a skill of 23.<br><br>2) All NON-TRADE skills have a level limit that cannot be exceeded.  The formula for all you weapon skills is [5 x (LEVEL + 1)].  Example:  You are level 3 using piercing.  The highest your piercing skill can be at level 3 is 20, or [5 x (3 + 1)].  For many, not all, skills the formula is the one stated here.<br><br>3) TRADE SKILLS can be increased as far, and as fast, as you have money, and time, to increase them.  However, you can only train them at your guild trainer to a skill of 20.  After a skill of 20, you can only increase the skill in a trade by doing the the work necessary to increase them.<br><br>4) As skills increase, your trainer will begin asking for money to increase them, at a skill of 16.  The cost of training a skill 1 point, at a trainer, will steadily increase the higher the skill goes.<br><br><br><br>-Do you get mana to cast spells?  See my list of skill Rangers learn above.  Look at LEVEL 9 for your answer.<br><br><br><br>-For Rangers, the most profitable trade skill to learn is FLETCHING/BOWERY.  This is because Rangers get the most worth out of a bow and arrow than any other class.  NOTE:  Do not learn this to make money.  You are learning it to make yourself better arrows/bows cheaper than you can buy them, if you can buy them at all.<br><br><br><br>-A Rusty Spear is fine if you have no money to buy anything else with.  Otherwise, look for upgrades.  A rusty spear is at the bottom rung of piercing weapons.  Just about anything else out there in the piercing category is better.  Note, I hope your using other weapons than piercing.  Rangers are known for their 1 hand slash weapons.  2 hand slash is good to keep a skill up in too.<br><br>Laars Silverton<br>30 Human Ranger</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
