		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.56]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Martelus&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>-At your NPC guild trainer is where you can increase skills, and learn new skill when you reach the appropriate level, by applying your training points to increase them.&nbsp;&nbsp;You gain 5 training points for every level you make.  Many Rangers like saving up there training points for when they reach a skill that is very important to increase quickly.  The skills most rangers save for are level 17 when they get DUAL WIELD, and level 20 when they get DOUBLE ATTACK.  NOTE:  No skill, except trade skills, can be increased over the level limit for you current level by training.<br><br><br>-Rangers begin casting spells at level 9.   When you reach 9 your mana bar will fill up.  Be sure to go to your trainer and train in your magic skills (ABJURATION, ALTERATION, CONJURATION, DIVINATION & EVOCATION).  You don't need to learn CHANNELLING.  You will already know it.<br><br><br>-The most useful trade skill for a Ranger is FLETCHING/BOWERY.  Not to make money with, but to use it to make good arrows and bows.  Arrows and bows made with the fletching skill are better than anything you will ever loot off of a monster or buy in a store.  NOTE:  Trade skills do not have a level limit like other skills.  If you have the money and time, you can increase your trade skills to 200 at level 1.<br><br><br>-If a rusty spear is all you can afford, then this is fine.  However, the rusty spear is at the bottom of to rung for piercing weapons.  Its about as bad as your gonna find.  Any other piercing weapon you find will be better than a rusty spear.  NOTE:  Be sure to increase one or two other weapon skills too.  Preferrably 1 hand slash and 2 hand slash.  Rangers are known for their 1 hand slash weapons.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
